==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tourney
<hw>Tour"ney</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>tornei</ets>, <ets>tornoi</ets>, F. <ets>tournoi</ets>, fr. OF.
<ets>torneier</ets>, <ets>tornoier</ets>, <ets>tournoier</ets>, to tit,
to tourney, F. <ets>tournoyer</ets> to turn round and round. See
<er>Turn</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>A tournament.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At tilt or <qex>tourney</qex> or like warlike game.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We hold a <qex>tourney</qex> here to-morrow morn,⟦br⟧
And there is scantly time for half the work.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tourney</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tourney
<hw>Tour"ney</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf.OF. <ets>torneier</ets>.
See <er>Tourney</er>, <pos>n.</pos> ]</ety> <def>To perform in
tournaments; to tilt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Well could he <qex>tourney</qex>, and in lists debate.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

